doc.after: A rocket powered aircraft or rocket plane is an aircraft that uses a rocket engine for propulsion sometimes in addition to airbreathing jet engines Rocket planes can achieve much higher speeds than similarly sized jet aircraft but typically for at most a few minutes of powered operation followed by a glide Unhindered by the need for oxygen from the atmosphere they are suitable for very high altitude flight They are also capable of delivering much higher acceleration and shorter takeoffs
